Jeffrey H. Smulyan J.D.Founder, Executive Chairman and Chief Executive Officer , Emmis Communications CorporationAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 8 Board Members in 8 different organizations across 5 different industries.See Board Relationships70$1,006,709As of Fiscal Year 2017
Background

		Mr. Jeffrey H. Smulyan, also known as Jeff, J.D., serves as an Operating Partner at Catalyst Investors. Mr. Smulyan founded Emmis Communications Corporation in 1979 and has been its Executive Chairman and Chief Executive Officer since 1981. He serves as the President and Chief Executive Officer of Emmis Operating Company. He is an Industry Advisor at BIA Digital Partners LP. He began working in radio in 1973 and has owned one or more radio stations since then. He was ... the owner and Chief Executive Officer of the Seattle Mariners baseball team. He has been an Executive Director of Emmis Communications Corp. since 1979. He served as President at Emmis Communications Corp from 1994 to August 2015. Mr. Smulyan serves as the Chairman of Emmis Operating Company. He serves as a Member of the Advisory Board at BIA Digital Partners II, L.P. He served as a Director of Finish Line Inc. from June 1992 to July 17, 2008. He sits on the Board of Trustees of Ball State University. He serves as a Trustee of University of Southern California. He was Note and Comment Editor of the USC Law Review at USC School of Law. He was the Chairman of the Board of Directors of the Radio Advertising Bureau. Mr. Smulyan was a Director of the National Association of Broadcasters. In 2000, he was honored with the American Women in Radio and Television's Silver Satellite Award, the National Association of Broadcasters' National Radio Award and as Radio Ink's “Radio Executive of the Year“ by a radio industry group. Mr. Smulyan was voted one of the Ten Most Influential Radio Executives in the past 20 Years in a poll in Radio and Records magazine. Mr. Smulyan is a cum laude graduate of the University of Southern California with a BA in History and Telecommunications. He earned a Juris Doctor degree from USC School of Law.Read Full Background




